{"id":314,"date":"2013-05-02T20:16:07","date_gmt":"2013-05-02T20:16:07","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/twelvershia.net\/?p=314"},"modified":"2013-05-02T20:16:07","modified_gmt":"2013-05-02T20:16:07","slug":"jafar-al-sadiq-stands-up-to-the-tyrant-in-the-books-of-sunnah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/2013\/05\/02\/jafar-al-sadiq-stands-up-to-the-tyrant-in-the-books-of-sunnah\/","title":{"rendered":"Ja`far al-Sadiq stands up to the tyrant in the books of Sunnah"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/imgstore.org\/a\/67hxw0egsgub?i=314\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ja`far al-Sadiq (rah) in the books of Ahlul-Sunnah is a brave honorable Imam from Ahlul-Bayt, Unlike the Shia version. Here is a narration from &#8220;Hilayt-ul-Awliya&#8217; wa Tabaqat al-Asfiya'&#8221; by al-Imam al-Hafiz abu Na`eem (rah):<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>\u062d\u062f\u062b\u0646\u0627 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645 \u060c \u062b\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0635\u0645\u0629 \u060c \u062b\u0646\u0627 \u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0631\u0648 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0642\u062f\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0627\u0632\u064a \u060c \u0642\u0627\u0644 : \u0648\u0642\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0630\u0628\u0627\u0628 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0646\u0635\u0648\u0631 \u0641\u0630\u0628\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u060c \u0641\u0639\u0627\u062f \u0641\u0630\u0628\u0647 \u062d\u062a\u0649 \u0623\u0636\u062c\u0631\u0647 \u060c \u0641\u062f\u062e\u0644 \u062c\u0639\u0641\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0647 \u060c \u0641\u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0644\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0646\u0635\u0648\u0631 : \u064a\u0627 \u0623\u0628\u0627 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0644\u0645 \u062e\u0644\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0630\u0628\u0627\u0628 \u061f \u0642\u0627\u0644 : \u0644\u064a\u0630\u0644 \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0628\u0627\u0628\u0631\u0629 .<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<strong>[Muhammad bin `Umar bin Salam told us, al-Hussayn ibn `Ismah told us, Ahmad bin `Amro bin al-Miqdam al-Razi said:<\/strong>\u00a0<strong>Flies were on the Khalifah al-Mansour, so he started to wave them away until he became bored.<\/strong><br \/>\n<strong>Then Ja`far bin Muhammad (al-Sadiq) entered on him, so al-Mansour asked\u00a0\u00a0him: &#8220;O aba `Abdillah, why did Allah create flies?&#8221;<\/strong><br \/>\n<strong>Ja`far replied: &#8220;To disgrace the tyrants.&#8221;]<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So how then can they make Ja`far (rah) appear like a coward who sticks to Taqiyyah and praises the rulers to be on their good side?<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<div class=\"mh-excerpt\"><p>Ja`far al-Sadiq (rah) in the books of Ahlul-Sunnah is a brave honorable Imam from Ahlul-Bayt, Unlike the Shia version. Here is a narration from &#8220;Hilayt-ul-Awliya&#8217; wa Tabaqat al-Asfiya&#8217;&#8221; by al-Imam al-Hafiz abu Na`eem (rah): \u062d\u062f\u062b\u0646\u0627 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645 <a class=\"mh-excerpt-more\" href=\"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/2013\/05\/02\/jafar-al-sadiq-stands-up-to-the-tyrant-in-the-books-of-sunnah\/\" title=\"Ja`far al-Sadiq stands up to the tyrant in the books of Sunnah\">[read more]<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":3845,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[8],"tags":[],"class_list":{"0":"post-314","1":"post","2":"type-post","3":"status-publish","4":"format-standard","5":"has-post-thumbnail","7":"category-taqiyyah"},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.twelvershia.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts